    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-05-07T16:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-05-07T16:32:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <head>474. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Thailand</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d474fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 792.551/5–758. Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_KE1"
                            >Kocher</persName> and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                            >Robertson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-05-07T17:32:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1958—5:32 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2779. Call of <persName corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> on President May 7, in
                    which <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>, Thai Ambassador and
                    Colonel Chalermchai participated, carried out in utmost cordiality.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d474fn2">A brief memorandum of conversation on this meeting by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> is <hi rend="italic"
                            >Ibid.</hi>, 792.13/5–1558.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> delivered to President greetings
                    from Thai Government and his thanks for hospitality and excellent medical
                    treatment received <persName>Walter Reed</persName>. He discussed with President
                    broad outlines Thai situation and problems including in most general fashion
                    need for increased aid. President indicated that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                        >Robertson</persName> and other appropriate US officials would have
                    subsequent discussions with him these matters.</p>
                <p>Extensive photographic coverage given meeting, which lasted about twenty minutes.
                    Department release re <persName corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> visit<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d474fn3">See Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bulletin</hi>, June 2, 1958, p. 912.</note> carried on <pb facs="1032"
                        n="1000" xml:id="pg_1000"/> VOA morning broadcast. According UP <persName
                        corresp="#p_TS1">Sarit</persName> told press President “most sympathetic”
                    with Thailand’s problems.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
